1. Create a layout for the screen
2. Create a class for the 2 paddles
   2.1 Assign the starting positions to the pads at X = -280 for paddle 1 and X = 280 for paddle 2
   2.1 Key bindings for paddle 1 and paddle 2
3. Create a ball class
   3.1 Assign shape, color
   3.2 Assign starting position on Y axis at X = 0
   3.3 Chart a random goto path towards paddle 2 (or randomize paddle too)
4. Game alg
   4.1 If path and paddle collieds before balls distance > 280 (assuming paddle 2), then char a new path
5. Create a scoreboard